.TH "of_changeset_action" 9 "of_changeset_action" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_changeset_action \- Add an action to the tail of the changeset list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_changeset_action
.BI "(struct of_changeset *ocs "  ","
.BI "unsigned long action "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "struct property *prop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ocs" 12
changeset pointer
.IP "action" 12
action to perform
.IP "np" 12
Pointer to device node
.IP "prop" 12
Pointer to property
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
On action being one of:
+ OF_RECONFIG_ATTACH_NODE
+ OF_RECONFIG_DETACH_NODE,
+ OF_RECONFIG_ADD_PROPERTY
+ OF_RECONFIG_REMOVE_PROPERTY,
+ OF_RECONFIG_UPDATE_PROPERTY
Returns 0 on success, a negative error value in case of an error.
